\pard\plain \fi720\sl288\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0 In a paragraph or so, describe an action, or a person, feeling strong emotion--joy, fear, grief. Try to make the rhythm and movement of the sentences embody or represent the physical reality you're writing about.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0
\par\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0 The brrrrum of the highway\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s rumble strip jolts him up. He grips the wheel, whips back into his lane, body-lurching, spine spiked by the equilibrium shift.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 He straightens his Subaru out, finds the center of his being, then the center of his lane. Here he will stay, wheel white-knuckled, breathing whole-body breaths while the soothing highway strum calms him down. Whump-whump, whump-whump go the pot-holes. This is Louisiana. Poplar pollen paints the concrete from here to Arkansas.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 GPS shows a red line and twenty added minutes\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 construction; Attakapas; 3 a.m.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 His eyes slouch, now sleeping.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 The brrrrum of the highway\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s rumble strip jolts him up.}}